Aghion, Jones, and Jones (2019)
\[\begin{aligned}
         Y_t &= A_t^{\sigma} K_t^{\alpha} L^{1-\alpha} \\
         \dot A_t &= K_t^{\beta} S^{\lambda} A_t^{\phi}
      \end{aligned}
\]
In task-based automation interpretations, (\(\alpha\)) and (\(\beta\)) reflect the fractions of tasks automated in goods and idea production. (aghion?) analyze when AI-driven automation can yield accelerating growth (“Type I”) or even a singularity (“Type II”). in their Cobb–Douglas setup a key threshold is (\(\gamma = \frac{\sigma}{1-\alpha}\cdot\frac{\beta}{1-\phi}\)), with a Type II singularity when (\(\gamma&gt;1\)).
